ay features turmeric TurmXTRA™ and vitamin C to support your general wellbeing.","descriptionTh":null,"extractedText":"Blackmores Concentrated Curcumin One-A-Day Tablets All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Concentrated Curcumin One-A-Day Size Size 30 tablets 60 tablets Good health changes everything - support your wellbeing daily with Blackmores Concentrated Curcumin One-A-Day. This one-a-day formula contains TurmXTRA™, a highly bioavailable form of curcumin, along with vitamin C. It helps maintain joint health, supports collagen formation, and promotes immune system health. Taken once daily with food, it’s a convenient way to help support your general wellness. Product Format Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Mild Joint Pain Inflammation Joint Health No Added Yeast No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy No Added Soya Bean Benefits & How To Use Benefits A convenient one-a-day formula to support joint health. Anti-inflammatory action. Relieves pain after exercise. Supports joint and joint cartilage health. Supports collagen formation. Antioxidant action to reduce free radicals formed in the body. Supports general health and wellbeing. Contains bioavailable TurmXTRA® 60N curcumin formulated for optimal absorption. Contains sulfites. Dosage Adults Take 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Do not use during pregnancy or breastfeeding. Do not use if you have pre-existing liver conditions. In very rare cases, Curcuma species may harm the liver. Stop use and see a doctor if you have yellowing skin/eyes or unusual: fatigue, nausea, appetite loss, abdominal pain, dark urine or itching. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. If you have any pre-existing conditions, or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains sulfites. Benefits Dosage Warnings A convenient one-a-day formula to support joint health. Anti-inflammatory action. Relieves pain after exercise. Supports joint and joint cartilage health. Supports collagen formation. Antioxidant action to reduce free radicals formed in the body. Supports general health and wellbeing. Contains bioavailable TurmXTRA® 60N curcumin formulated for optimal absorption. Contains sulfites. Adults Take 1 tablet once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Do not use during pregnancy or breastfeeding. Do not use if you have pre-existing liver conditions. In very rare cases, Curcuma species may harm the liver. Stop use and see a doctor if you have yellowing skin/eyes or unusual: fatigue, nausea, appetite loss, abdominal pain, dark urine or itching. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. If you have any pre-existing conditions, or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains sulfites. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients per capsule: Curcuma longa (as TurmXTRA® 60N) extract dry conc. 158 mg equivalent dry rhizome 3900 mg (3.9 g) standardised to curcumin 150 mg Ascorbic acid (vitamin C) 45 mg Concentrated Curcumin One-A-Day Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Taiwan Region Thailand Vietnam International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Taiwan Region Thailand Vietnam Terms & Policies Privacy Policy & Practices Terms Of Purchase Terms of Ser