riptionTh":null,"extractedText":"Blackmores Evening Primrose Oil Capsules All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Evening Primrose Oil Size Size 125 capsules 190 capsules Good health changes everything—Blackmores Evening Primrose Oil is a natural source of omega-6 fatty acids to help support skin health from within. This cold-pressed oil helps maintain skin hydration, relieve skin dryness, and support skin health. It is also traditionally used to relieve inflammation and support general health and wellbeing. Evening primrose oil is a source of gamma-linolenic acid (GLA), which plays a role in maintaining the structure and function of the skin. Taken daily, this high-quality oil is rigorously tested for purity and quality, making it a reliable choice for those seeking plant-based skin support. Product Format Capsule Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Skin Health Inflammation No Added Wheat No Added Gluten No Added Yeast No Added Dairy Benefits & How To Use Benefits Evening primrose oil (EPO) is a source of the omega-6 essential fatty acids, gamma-linolenic acid (GLA) and linoleic acid (LA). Lifestyle factors such as excess saturated fats in the diet and stress levels also affect GLA metabolism. Provides omega-6 essential fatty acids which provide anti-inflammatory support. Provides support for skin health and hydration. Reduces skin dryness. Relieves inflammation. Supports general health and wellbeing. Dosage Adults For general health and wellbeing: Take 2 capsules, once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. For skin and as an anti-inflammatory: Take 2 capsules, twice a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding talk to your health professional before use. If you have any pre-existing conditions, or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains phenylalanine, soya bean products and sulfites. Benefits Dosage Warnings Evening primrose oil (EPO) is a source of the omega-6 essential fatty acids, gamma-linolenic acid (GLA) and linoleic acid (LA). Lifestyle factors such as excess saturated fats in the diet and stress levels also affect GLA metabolism. Provides omega-6 essential fatty acids which provide anti-inflammatory support. Provides support for skin health and hydration. Reduces skin dryness. Relieves inflammation. Supports general health and wellbeing. Adults For general health and wellbeing: Take 2 capsules, once a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. For skin and as an anti-inflammatory: Take 2 capsules, twice a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. If symptoms persist, talk to your health professional. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding talk to your health professional before use. If you have any pre-existing conditions, or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains phenylalanine, soya bean products and sulfites. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients per capsule: Evening primrose oil (EPO) 1000 mg (1 g) providing gamma-linolenic acid (GLA) 100 mg Evening Primrose Oil Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Taiwan Region Thailand Vietnam International Markets China Hong Kong SAR iHerb Indonesia Korea Malaysia New Zealand Singapore Ta