to help supplement the nutritional needs of growing toddlers.","descriptionTh":null,"extractedText":"Blackmores Junior Milk Drink Powder All Products Shop All Products New Products Best Sellers Vegan Certified Women&#x27;s Health Men&#x27;s Health Kid&#x27;s Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition By Category Arthritis, Joint & Bone Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutritional Oils Heart Health Infant & Toddler Nutrition Kids&#x27; Health Men&#x27;s Health Multivitamins Muscle Support Nails, Hair & Skin Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health By Ingredient Calcium CoQ10 Curcumin Echinacea Fish Oil & Omega 3 Glucosamine Iron Magnesium Probiotics Selenium Vitamin B Vitamin C Vitamin D Vitamin E Zinc Health Hub By Categories By Type Latest Articles Action Plans Arthritis, Bone & Joint Beauty & Skincare Brain & Cognitive Health Cold, Flu & Immunity Digestive & Gut Health Energy Everyday Health Eye Health Fish & Nutrition Oils Heart & Cardiovascular Health Kids & Infant Health Men&#x27;s Health Muscle Support & Fitness Preconception, Pregnancy & Breastfeeding Recipes Stress Relief & Sleep Support Women&#x27;s Health Action Plans Articles Recipes Latest Articles About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Pillars Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Contact us Ask A Naturopath Our Newsroom Blackmores Subscribe Search Home Chevron Icon Horizontal products Chevron Icon Horizontal Blackmores Junior Milk Drink Size Size 900 grams Blackmores Junior Milk Drink Stage 4 is specially formulated for children aged 2 years and over. Made with premium Australian cow’s milk and enriched with essential vitamins and minerals, it supports growth and development when enjoyed as part of a healthy, balanced diet. Product Format Powder Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Infant & Toddler Nutrition Halal Certified Benefits & How To Use Benefits Formulated by Blackmores, Australia’s most trusted vitamin brand*, with over 90 years of expertise in natural health, this Junior Milk Drink is designed to supplement the nutritional needs of growing toddlers as part of a balanced diet. Suitable for children 2 years and over. Supports healthy growth & development with 16 essential nutrients** Immune system support from 8 ingredients (Iron, Zinc, Folate, Vitamins A, B6, B12, C, D) Helps support cognitive function and development with iron, zinc and iodine Contains Prebiotic FOS & GOS and Probiotics B.lactis HN019 Contains Lutein No added artificial flavours or preservatives Made from Premium Fresh Australian Milk One serve of Blackmores Junior Milk Drink provides your child with at least 24% of the recommended dietary intake^ of Vitamins A, B1, B2, B3, B6, folate (B9), B12, C, D, E, calcium, iron, iodine, magnesium, phosphorous and zinc. *Reader’s Digest Trusted Brands Survey, Australia, 2009–2024. ** In young children, in conjunction with a healthy balanced diet and when consumed per 227 mL. Prepared Junior Milk Drink: Supports Healthy Growth & Development - Vitamins A, C, D, E, & Calcium, Iodine, Iron, Magnesium, Phosphorus, Zinc, Folate, B1, B2, B3, B6 and B12. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. This product is a formulated supplementary food for young children and is intended to be used as part of a balanced diet. Not suitable for children under 12 months. To be used to supplement the normal diet when energy and nutrient intakes may not be adequate to meet a child’s nutritional needs. CONTAINS MILK AND SOY. MAY CONTAIN FISH. Feeding Guide FEEDING GUIDE - TO PREPARE ONE FEED Age of infant Cooled boiled water (mL) Level scoops of formula Formula feeds per day 12 - 24 months 200 mL 4 2-3 One level scoop = 8.8 g of formula. HOW TO PREPARE Wash hands and all equipment before preparing Blackmores® Junior Milk Drink. Measure out the required amount of previously boiled and cooled water, and powder by consulting the SERVING GUIDE Using only the scoop provided, lightly fill one measurement of the powder and use levelling blade on tin. Pour powder into the previously boiled and cooled water, stir or shake until the powder is dissolved. Always prepare each bottle separately and freshly for every feed. Discard unused portions; do not keep for later feeding. Benefits Warnings Feeding Guide Formulated by Blackmores, Australia’s most trusted vitamin brand*, with over 90 years of expertise in natural health, this Junior Milk Drink is designed to supplement the nutritional needs of growing toddlers as part of a balanced diet. Suitable for children 2 years and over. Supports healthy growth & development with 16 essential nutrients** Immune system support from 8 ingredients (Iron, Zinc, Folate, Vitamins A, B6, B12, C, D) Helps support cognitive function and development with iron, zinc and iodine Contains Prebiotic FOS & GOS and Probiotics B.lactis HN019 Contains Lutein No added artificial flavours or preservatives Made from Premium Fresh Australian Milk One serve of Blackmores Junior Milk Drink provides your child with at least 24% of the recommended dietary intake^ of Vitamins A, B1, B2, B3, B6, folate (B9), B12, C, D, E, calcium, iron, iodine, magnesium, phosphorous and zinc. *Reader’s Digest Trusted Brands Survey, Australia, 2009–2024. ** In young children, in conjunction with a healthy balanced diet and when consumed per 227 mL. Prepared Junior Milk Drink: Supports Healthy Growth & Development - Vitamins A, C, D, E, & Calcium, Iodine, Iron, Magnesium, Phosphorus, Zinc, Folate, B1, B2, B3, B6 and B12. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. This product is a formulated supplementary food for young children and is intended to be used as part of a balanced diet. Not suitable for children under 12 months. To be used to supplement the normal diet when energy and nutrient intakes may not be adequate to meet a child’s nutritional needs. CONTAINS MILK AND SOY. MAY CONTAIN FISH. FEEDING GUIDE - TO PREPARE ONE FEED Age of infant Cooled boiled water (mL) Level scoops of formula Formula feeds per day 12 - 24 months 200 mL 4 2-3 One level scoop = 8.8 g of formula. HOW TO PREPARE Wash hands and all equipment before preparing Blackmores® Junior Milk Drink. Measure out the required amount of previously boiled and cooled water, and powder by consulting the SERVING GUIDE Using only the scoop provided, lightly fill one measurement of the powder and use levelling blade on tin. Pour powder into the previously boiled and cooled water, stir or shake until the powder is dissolved. Always prepare each bottle separately and freshly for every feed. Discard unused portions; do not keep for later feeding. The Blackmores Difference Nutritional Information Servings per can: Approx. 26 Serving size: Approx. 227 mL (34 g and 200 mL water) Average quantity per 227 mL prepared Toddler Milk Drink % *RDI per serve Average quantity per 100 mL Energy 672 kJ 296 kJ Protein, total 6.00 g 2.64 g Gluten Not detected Not detected Fat, total 7.14 g 3.15 g saturated 3.54 g 1.56 g trans 0.17 g 0.07 g monounsaturated 2.55 g 1.12 g polyunsaturated 0.88 g 0.39 g Docosahexaenoic Acid (DHA) 10.2 mg 4.49 mg Alpha-linolenic Acid (ALA) 68.0 mg 29.9 mg Arachidonic Acid (ARA) 10.2 mg 4.49 mg Linoleic Acid 0.68 g 0.30 g Carbohydrate 17.3 g 7.62 g sugars 14.0 g 6.17 g Dietary Fibre, total 1.33 g 0.59 g Galacto-oligosaccharide (GOS) 1.20 g 0.53 g Fructo-oligosaccharide (GOS) 130 g 57.3 g Sodium 60 mg 26.4 mg Potassium 224 mg 98.7 mg Vitamins Vitamin A 76.5 µg RE 26% 33.7 µg RE Thiamin (vitamin B1) 0.21 mg 42% 0.09 mg Riboflavin (vitamin B2) 0.34 mg 43% 0.15 mg Niacin (vitamin B3) 1.36 mg 27% 0.60mg Vitamin B6 0.21 mg 30% 0.09 mg Folate (vitamin B9) 34.0 µg 34% 15.0 µg Vitamin B12 0.50 µg 50% 0.22 µg Vitamin C 15.0 mg 50% 6.61 mg Vitamin D 1.50 µg 30% 0.66 µg Vitamin E 2.50 mg α-TE 50% 1.10 mg α-TE Minerals Calcium 221 mg 32% 97.4 mg Iodine 20.4 µg 29% 8.99 µg Iron 2.60 mg 43% 1.15 mg Magnesium 20.4 mg 26% 8.99 mg Phosphorous 146 mg 29% 64.3 mg Zinc 1.10 mg 24% 0.48 mg Other Lutein 37.5 µg 16.5 µg Probiotics Bifidobacterium lactis HN019 24.0 Million CFU 10.6 Million CFU # Every 28g of fat contains 4.2 g of beta palmitate as oleic palmitic oleic (OPO) ^ RDI: Recommended Dietary intake for children 1-3 years (FSANZ- Food Standards Australia New Zealand) Ingredients Milk Solids, Vegetable Oil Blend# ( Soy ), Maltodextrin, Galacto-oligosaccharide (GOS) ( Milk ), Fructo-Oligosaccharide (FOS), Acidity Regulator (Potassium Citrate), Emulsifier ( Soy Lecithin), Arachidonic Acid Oil (ARA) ( Milk ), Docosahexaenoic Acid Oil (DHA) ( Milk ), Probiotic ( Bifidobacterium lactis HN019), Lutein, Antioxidants (Ascorbyl Palmitate, Tocopherol Concentrate, Mixed). Minerals (Magnesium Sulphate, Tri Calcium Phosphate, Calcium Carbonate, Ferric Pyrophosphate, Zinc Sulphate, Potassium Iodide). Vitamins [Sodium Ascorbate (Vitamin C), D-alpha Tocopheryl Acetate (Vitamin E) ( Soy ), Nicotinamide (Vitamin B3), Retinyl Acetate (Vitamin A), Folic Acid (Vitamin B9), Cyanocobalamin (Vitamin B12), Pyridoxine Hydrochloride (Vitamin B6), Thiamine Hydrochloride (Vitamin B1), Riboflavin (Vitamin B2), Cholecalciferol (Vitamin D)]. CONTAINS MILK AND SOY. MAY CONTAIN FISH. Frequently asked questions about Junior Milk Drink How can I learn more about the Blackmores Infant Nutrition Range? You can learn more about the range and read our FAQs here . Alternatively, contact our Naturopathic Advisory Team on 1800 803 760 . What is Blackmores Junior Milk Drink (Stage 4)? Blackmores Junior Milk Drink stage 4 is specially formulated to help supplement the growth and development and energy needs of growing toddlers. Made with premium fresh Australian milk and enriched with a unique blend of nutrients, it is suitable for children from 2 years of age. When enjoyed as part of a healthy balanced diet it provides essential vitamins and minerals to support your child’s growth and development. Just one serve delivers at least 24% of the recommended dietary intake for Vitamins A, B1, B2, B3, B6, Folate (B9), B12, C, D, and E, as well as Calcium, Iron, Iodine, Magnesium, Phosphorus, and Zinc (FSANZ RDI for children aged 1–3 years). How many feeds a day can I give my toddler? Blackmores Junior Milk Drink is a formulated supplementary food for young children aged 2 years and over. It can help support your child’s nutritional needs when energy and nutrient intake may be inadequate and should be enjoyed as part of a balanced diet. Two to three serves a day provide a tasty milk drink to supplement your toddler’s diet. Do you add artifical flavour? No. We do not add artificial flavours or preservatives. How do I prepare my baby’s formula? Please look at both methods detailed below and choose the one that is best for your family. If you are unable to reliably store your baby’s formula in cool, dry conditions, your baby has health issues or was born prematurely, please consider using the hot water preparation with water no cooler than 70°C. Preparing formula with hot water Preparing formula with cooled water Preparing formula with cooled water (Vietnamese) The WHO and other many other health advisory bodies advise that best practice is to boil the kettle and allow it to cool for just under half an hour to reach approximately 70°C. You then add the powder to the water and can cool the prepared milk down to feeding temperature quickly by running the bottle under the cold water tap or placing in a jug of cool water. Please be sure to check that the milk has cooled down to the right temperature before you feed your baby. It should feel just slightly warm on your skin. How long can the product be used once opened? We recommend you use the contents of the tin within 4 weeks of opening. Junior Milk Drink Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Imp","productImportId":"09a06f5b-ddbb-4930-b1a5-2cf26ede1133","aiFactCorrection":{"notes":"Removed nutrition panel noise, fatty acids, prebiotic fibre values and lutein; retained only matching canonical vitamins/minerals with per-serve doses from structured table.","responseId":"26497428-30bf-96aa-9170-cde1f03f17c9","correctedAt":"2026-05-18T16:50:21.349Z","originalFactCount":27,"correctedFactCount":16},"activeIngredientCount":27,"structuredIngredients":[],"candidateSupplierReason":"Blackmores Thailand product pages expose structured active ingredient tables, product images and FDA advertising approval text."},"affiliate_status":"none","normalized_title":"blackmores_junior_milk_drink","product_audience":"both","validation_status":"pass","validation_reasons":[],"validation_summary":"16 matchable canonical facts.","availability_status":"unknown","external_product_id":null,"fda_approval_number":null,"affiliate_checked_at":null,"normalized_brand_name":"blackmores","validation_checked_at":"2026-05-21T13:09:46.414+00:00","availability_cached_at":null,"product_data_expires_at":null}'::jsonb, '{"status":"approved","version":2,"changeNote":"approve_clean_blackmores_validation_pass","validation":{"status":"pass","reasons":[],"summary":"16 matchable canonical facts.","checkedAt":"2026-05-21T13:10:33.098Z","matchableFactCount":16},"sourceSnapshotPatch":null,"manufacturerCountriesChanged":false}'::jsonb, '2026-05-21T13:10:33.101Z'::timestamptz),
