help reduce the occurrence of common colds. This formula supports general health and wellbeing, and is suitable for everyday use to help maintain your body’s natural defences. Product Format Tablet Always read the label and follow the directions for use. Read the warnings before purchase. Support For Immune System Health Common Colds & Flu Respiratory Health Halal Certified No Added Yeast No Added Gluten No Added Wheat No Added Dairy Benefits & How To Use Benefits A combination formula with echinacea, vitamin A, C, E & zinc. Supports healthy immune system function. Reduces the severity and duration of common cold symptoms. Echinacea is traditionally used in Western Herbal Medicine to: Help reduce occurrence of symptoms of upper respiratory tract infections. Help reduce occurrence of common colds. Dosage Adults Take 1 tablet three times a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Warnings Always read the label and follow the directions for use. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding, talk to your health professional before use. WARNING - Stop taking this medication if you experience tingling, burning or numbness and see your healthcare practitioner as soon as possible (Contains vitamin B6). Adults only. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. Dietary supplements may only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains fish and soya bean products. Benefits Dosage Warnings A combination formula with echinacea, vitamin A, C, E & zinc. Supports healthy immune system function. Reduces the severity and duration of common cold symptoms. Echinacea is traditionally used in Western Herbal Medicine to: Help reduce occurrence of symptoms of upper respiratory tract infections. Help reduce occurrence of common colds. Adults Take 1 tablet three times a day, or as prescribed by a health professional. Take with food. Always read the label and follow the directions for use. If you are pregnant or breastfeeding, talk to your health professional before use. WARNING - Stop taking this medication if you experience tingling, burning or numbness and see your healthcare practitioner as soon as possible (Contains vitamin B6). Adults only. If symptoms persist talk to your health professional. Dietary supplements may only be of assistance if dietary intake is inadequate. If you have any pre-existing conditions or are on any medications always talk to your health professional before use. Some products should be ceased at least two weeks before any elective surgery, please confirm with your health professional. Contains fish and soya bean products. The Blackmores Difference Ingredients Active ingredients per tablet: Echinacea purpurea (echinacea) extract dry conc. 100 mg equivalent dry root 600 mg Ascorbic acid (vitamin C) 250 mg Betacarotene 3 mg d-alpha-tocopheryl acid succinate 41.3 mg equivalent vitamin E 50 IU Pyridoxine hydrochloride 13 mg equivalent pyridoxine (vitamin B6) 10.7 mg Zinc amino acid chelate 6.5 mg equivalent zinc 1.3 mg Calcium pantothenate 28 mg equivalent pantothenic acid (vitamin B5) 25.7 mg Show More Echinacea ACE + Zinc Reviews Let&#x27;s stay in touch Instagram Facebook TikTok LinkedIn Back To Top About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom About Blackmores About Blackmores Our Heritage Our Approach Our Impact Our Sustainability Approach Our People & Culture Our Careers Our Ambassadors & Partners Our Newsroom Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmores Professional Blackmores Institute Blackmores Education Our Brands & Products Shop Our Products Shop Best Sellers BioCeuticals Blackmore